HEADWORD: Demimonde
<hw>Dem`i*monde"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.;
<ets>demi</ets> + <ets>monde</ets> world, L. <ets>mundus</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Persons of doubtful reputation; esp., women who are kept as
mistresses, though not public prostitutes; demireps.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Literary demimonde</b></col>, <cd>writers of the lowest
kind.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deminatured</ent>⟦br⟧
